xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"John Parris\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3135:\"<p>Since version .70, I&#8217;ve made several improvements to the theme. The notable improvements are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Cleaned up templates and sidebar code and removed some duplicate code.</li>\n<li>Added new filters:\n<ul>\n<li>alienship_content_container_class and alienship_sidebar_container_class (allows you to change span* container/sidebar classes and/or add your own classes)</li>\n<li>alienship_breadcrumb_container_class (allows you to change the breadcrumb div container class)</li>\n</ul>\n<li>New template tags:</li>\n<ul>\n<li>alienship_post_comments_link (displays the Comment link on a post)</li>\n<li>alienship_entry_title function. (displays post and page titles)</li>\n</ul>\n<li>Improved the site title and post title display headings. On the home page, blog index, and archives, titles are displayed using the H2 tag while the site name has the H1 tag. When displaying a single post page, the post title is displayed with the H1 tag and the site name is wrapped in a classed paragraph tag.</li>\n<li>Included a simple CSS file for moving the sidebar to the left of the content. Include the file layouts/sidebar-content.css in your theme to move the sidebar to the left.</li>\n<li>Added support for custom/custom_functions.php.</li>\n<li>Removed the Cabin font.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>The road ahead</h2>\n<p>I&#8217;ve learned some things working with Alien Ship over the last couple months, and I&#8217;ve learned what I do and do not like about the theme. I set out to make this a starter theme that helps jumpstart development, and as I&#8217;ve built several sites using the theme, I&#8217;ve found ways to improve it so that it&#8217;s easier to get started on new sites and easier to update down the road. Sometimes I&#8217;ve wanted to gut many features, or substantially change existing ones, and these needs helped me see where to improve Alien Ship.</p>\n<p>With that in mind, I&#8217;ve been porting Alien Ship over to a modular framework design. Alien Ship 1.0 will be built on top of this framework. It&#8217;s pretty nice and I think you&#8217;ll like it. I&#8217;ll write more about this soon.</p>\n<p> I&#8217;ll also be moving to a versioning system that more accurately reflects major, minor, and revision changes instead of the crap I&#8217;ve been using thus far. I won&#8217;t be dropping breaking changes in minor release versions unless necessary.</p>\n<h2>What this means for you</h2>\n<p>If you run the theme straight up without any custom modifications, pretty much nothing changes for you. You&#8217;ll be able to replace your alienship folder with the new one and everything should remain the same. </p>\n<p>If you&#8217;ve made some changes or you&#8217;re using a child theme, some things will likely change. As the release of 1.0 nears, I&#8217;ll write about the things that may affect you.</p>\n<h2>Bare bones</h2>\n<p>Around the same time that Alien Ship 1.0 drops, I&#8217;ll be releasing another theme built on the framework that is stripped down with no theme options and will have minimal styling. It&#8217;ll truly be a starting theme for developers, with a nice modular architecture and a clean slate.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:80:\"http://www.johnparris.com/alienship/latest-improvements-and-the-road-ahead/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5