4 09:56:59','2013-06-14 16:56:59',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','84','','','2013-06-14 10:17:39','2013-06-14 17:17:39','',0,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/?p=84',9,'nav_menu_item','',0),(28,1,'2013-06-14 09:30:46','2013-06-14 16:30:46','','Partner Account','','inherit','closed','closed','','9-revision-3','','','2013-06-14 09:30:46','2013-06-14 16:30:46','',9,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/9-revision-3/',10,'revision','',0),(29,1,'2013-06-14 09:29:45','2013-06-14 16:29:45','','Orders','','inherit','closed','closed','','11-revision-2','','','2013-06-14 09:29:45','2013-06-14 16:29:45','',11,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/11-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(30,1,'2013-06-14 09:36:32','2013-06-14 16:36:32','<h2>You\'ve reached the RPI ShowRoom Partner Portal</h2>\r\nThere\'s not a lot working just yet. <a href=\"/partner/partner-account/partner-keys/\">Partner Keys</a>over there on the top rightare just beginning to work in this portal.\r\n\r\nThere\'s also a short example of the sort of API documentation we\'ll put here in the <a href=\"/angel-api-2/structure/all-or-part/\">All or Part</a>section taken from the Word API document.','Welcome','','publish','closed','closed','','welcome','','','2013-06-17 10:25:58','2013-06-17 17:25:58','',0,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/?page_id=30',9,'page','',0),(31,1,'2013-06-14 09:35:57','2013-06-14 16:35:57','','Welcome','','inherit','closed','closed','','30-revision','','','2013-06-14 09:35:57','2013-06-14 16:35:57','',30,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/30-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(32,1,'2013-06-14 09:37:44','2013-06-14 16:37:44','This is the page you use to maintain your partner keys. It\'s a good idea to use different keys for different applications and versions. Keys can be disabled by providing a Message which begins \"** \".\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;\">The ** triggers an error when the key is used.</span><span style=\"font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;\"></span>These messages will be returned as \"** invalid: <em>** your message here</em>\" when that key is used. Your application may use status calls to fetch both the Note and the Msg associated with any key. Other than the initial ** the contents of both and what your application does with them are entirely up to you.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Keys which have a ** disabling message are highlighted in red below. </span><span style=\"font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;\">All disabled keys are listed after all valid keys. Within that order k</span><span style=\"font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;\">eys are listed alphabetically by their Notes.</span>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #888888; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;\">Note in most browsers typing a return into the Note or Message box of a key is the same as hitting the Update button for that key.</span></p>','Partner Keys','','publish','closed','closed','','partner-keys','','','2013-06-17 13:43:17','2013-06-17 20:43:17','',9,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/partner-account/partner-keys/',4,'page','',0),(33,1,'2013-06-14 09:37:44','2013-06-14 16:37:44','','Partner Keys','','inherit','closed','closed','','32-revision','','','2013-06-14 09:37:44','2013-06-14 16:37:44','',32,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/32-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(83,1,'2013-06-14 09:56:59','2013-06-14 16:56:59',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','83','','','2013-06-14 10:17:39','2013-06-14 17:17:39','',0,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/?p=83',8,'nav_menu_item','',0),(35,1,'2013-06-14 09:35:57','2013-06-14 16:35:57','','Orders','','inherit','closed','closed','','11-revision-3','','','2013-06-14 09:35:57','2013-06-14 16:35:57','',11,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/11-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(36,1,'2013-06-03 23:51:31','2013-06-03 23:51:31','Partner Portal Home page.','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','4-revision-2','','','2013-06-03 23:51:31','2013-06-03 23:51:31','',4,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/4-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(82,1,'2013-06-14 09:55:40','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2013-06-14 09:55:40','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/?p=82',8,'nav_menu_item','',0),(39,1,'2013-06-14 09:40:15','2013-06-14 16:40:15','','Angel API','','inherit','closed','closed','','38-revision','','','2013-06-14 09:40:15','2013-06-14 16:40:15','',38,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/38-revision/',8,'revision','',0),(40,1,'2013-06-14 09:42:54','2013-06-14 16:42:54','<p class=\"MsoNormal\">This API accepts requests as Posts only. All exchanges take place on a certificate encoded channel. To insure privacy all input are accepted in an https secured message body, not in the URL itself. Indeed, all action URLs POST to the same location. Currently that POST URL is: <a href=\"https://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/orderup\">https://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/orderup</a>.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">To application input to the API may be presented as JSON or as FORM encoded content of a POST. Data field names and types are the same in either form. In all cases the response will be in JSON. More concisely a well formed POST can accept mime encodings of either \"application/JSON\" or \"multipart/form-data\" for the parameters described here. Responses will always be \"application/JSON\".</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Images are typically accepted through form encoded file uploads. The actions of order-creation, order-item-addition, item-image-uploads and order-placement can be accomplished in one or more POSTS as convenient to the application. The only restriction is that not more that 30 minutes may elapse between order-creation and order-placement.</p>','Structure','','publish','closed','closed','','structure','','','2013-06-17 11:09:49','2013-06-17 18:09:49','',191,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/angel-api-2/structure/',3,'page','',0),(41,1,'2013-06-14 09:42:54','2013-06-14 16:42:54','The default data encoding used by order submission is exactly the same encoding used in HTML POST forms. This allows a large amount of data to be securely encrypted and delivered to the server in one large or many small steps. A standard browser delivers <strong>multipart/form-data</strong>when POST\'ing forms and always when doing file-uploads.\r\n\r\nAs the HTML examples show it is straight forward to drive the order interface directly from a browser session. Most application building environments provide the means to construct the POST information directly.\r\n\r\nThe naming conventions used in this API are aimed at allowing a flat list of names to form the hierarchy needed to express an order with multiple items each of which may require multiple assets to personalize the result. There are no upper case letters in any field name. Field names are qualified beginning with words separated by a  \'_\' (under bar not a \'-\', dash) from the root name. These qualifiers allow different portions of the order to be addressed without the use of container elements. ','Fields','','publish','closed','closed','','fields','','','2013-06-17 11:45:40','2013-06-17 18:45:40','',191,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/angel-api-2/fields/',5,'page','',0),(42,1,'2013-06-14 09:42:54','2013-06-14 16:42:54','The error messages summarize and complain about fields under their field-names in a JSON response. Every item causing a problem will start the response with ** . If a non-error response is called for it will not begin ** .\r\n\r\nErrors may provide more detail. The message will contain none, missing, invalid, or incomplete following the initial **. Detail information will follow the summary word with a : , separator. Heres an example where a file field was sent with no file content.\r\n<pre>{</pre>\r\n<pre><b>order</b>:\"** incomplete\",</pre>\r\n<pre><b>orderkey</b>:\"RA98C1876O8D170EA3296B215BB263CFADBA23AD12\",</pre>\r\n<pre><b>item-1-inset</b>:\"** missing: ** Upload failed UPLOAD_ERR_NO_FILE\"</pre>\r\n<pre>}</pre>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWithin errors a nested object named for the portion of the step that failed contains messages named for all failing fields. For example if an order is started in which the cName is blank and the phone number is only 7 digits will respond:\r\n<pre>{</pre>\r\n<pre><b>order</b>:\"placed\",</pre>\r\n<pre><b>orderkey</b>:\"RA98C1848O0E532A06D699ED3283A9CB696ED5F4C5\",</pre>\r\n<pre><b>label-phone</b>:\"** invalid\",</pre>\r\n<pre><b>label-email</b>:\"** invalid\"</pre>\r\n<pre>}</pre>\r\n&nbsp;','Responses','','publish','closed','closed','','responses','','','2013-06-14 15:34:26','2013-06-14 22:34:26','',40,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/angel-api-2/responses/',4,'page','',0),(43,1,'2013-06-14 09:42:54','2013-06-14 16:42:54','Once an order is accepted real goods and services will be expended to create and ship the result. The authorization that allows this is a potential point of abuse. RPI supplies several tools and checks which can help you to manage your authority and applications which use these services.\r\n\r\nRPI provides unique keys to help you control the applications you are running as well as the applications and product models you are developing. These keys always refer to a specific Partner, Product Model or Order. They are generated in a way that guarantees they are unique and at the same time not reasonably guessable.\r\n\r\nBy controlling which customers and applications are given which keys you remain in control of each item separately. Giving applications different Model keys for the same product allows you to disable that product in a specific application without affecting your other commerce. Attaching partner unique partner keys to a version of an application provides a way to disable that specific version in the field and provide a message or action to the application. Only order keys are one-to-one. An order key is the only valid way to continue, cancel or check on a order in progress.','Security Keys','','publish','closed','closed','','security-keys','','','2013-06-17 11:16:52','2013-06-17 18:16:52','',191,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/angel-api-2/keys-and-security/',4,'page','',0),(44,1,'2013-06-14 09:42:54','2013-06-14 16:42:54','Status request are not part of the order process. They serve to aid more dynamic applications in determining what offerings are available at a specific time. The status of all keys include the both the Note and any Message the Partner has provided for that key.\r\n\r\nWhile simple applications might choose to use their given keys until they fail a more sophisticated shopping experience could be controlled through the keys and group names defined in the partner portal. Status inquiries can define the available products in real time before any errors have been encountered.','Status','','publish','closed','closed','','status','','','2013-06-17 12:03:14','2013-06-17 19:03:14','',191,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/angel-api-2/status/',6,'page','',0),(45,1,'2013-06-14 09:42:54','2013-06-14 16:42:54','','Structure','','inherit','closed','closed','','40-revision','','','2013-06-14 09:42:54','2013-06-14 16:42:54','',40,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/40-revision/',10,'revision','',0),(46,1,'2013-06-14 09:44:07','2013-06-14 16:44:07','To begin an order all of the following customer information must be supplied. Until this information is validated no information for the order is recorded. Once these values are complete an order-key is generated and is required in all POSTs and supplied in all responses until order-placed is received.\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n<table width=\"686\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"127\"></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"228\"><b>Shipping label</b><b></b></td>\r\n<td width=\"331\"><b>Requirement </b><b>(optional)</b><b></b></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"127\"><b>order_pref</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"228\">(opt) Partner reference information for this order. Holds a string that is accessible to the application when examining this order.</td>\r\n<td width=\"331\">Up to 1024 characters</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"127\"><b>order_note</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"228\">(opt) Note that appears on shipping label.</td>\r\n<td width=\"331\">Up to 1024 characters</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"127\"><b>order_shipping</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"228\">Shipping designator (UPS)</td>\r\n<td width=\"331\">Valid designator from list (USP,mail,FedEx?)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"127\"><b>label_name</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"228\">Customer name</td>\r\n<td width=\"331\">[A-Za-z]+(\\\'[A-Za-z]+)?(\\s*\\-?\\s*[A-Za-z]+)?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"127\"><b>label_email</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"228\">Customer Email</td>\r\n<td width=\"331\">[A-Za-z0-9._%+-]+@[A-Za-z0-9.-]+\\.[A-Za-z]{2,4}</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"127\"><b>label_phone</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"228\">Customer Phone</td>\r\n<td width=\"331\">(1-?)?(\\([2-9]\\d{2}\\)|[2-9]\\d{2})\\s*-?\\s*[2-9]\\d{2}\\s*-?\\s*\\d{4}</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"127\"><b>label_company</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"228\">(opt) Receiving Company</td>\r\n<td width=\"331\">\\w[-\\w\\\'\\.]*(\\s*[-\\w\\\'\\.]+)*</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"127\"><b>label_addr1</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"228\">Customer Address Line 1<b></b></td>\r\n<td width=\"331\">[\\w\\s.,@&amp;\\-#*]*?[A-Za-z]{2}[\\w\\s.,@&amp;\\-#*]*</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"127\"><b>label_addr2</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"228\">Customer Address Line 2</td>\r\n<td width=\"331\">[\\w\\s.,@&amp;\\-#*]*?[A-Za-z]{2}[\\w\\s.,@&amp;\\-#*]*</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"127\"><b>label_city</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"228\">Customer City</td>\r\n<td width=\"331\">[a-z\\s.-]*?[A-Za-z]{2}[a-z\\s.-]</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"127\"><b>label_state</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"228\">Customer State</td>\r\n<td width=\"331\">[A-Za-z]{2}</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"127\"><b>label_postal</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"228\">Customer Postal Code</td>\r\n<td width=\"331\">\\d{5}(-\\d{4})?(\\~\\d{1,3})?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"127\"><b>label_country</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"228\">(optional) Customer Country (USA default)</td>\r\n<td width=\"331\">\\w[-\\w\\\'\\.]*(\\s*[-\\w\\\'\\.]+)*</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>','Beginning an Order','','publish','closed','closed','','beginning-an-order','','','2013-06-17 11:51:57','2013-06-17 18:51:57','',41,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/angel-api-2/fields/beginning-an-order/',8,'page','',0),(47,1,'2013-06-14 09:44:07','2013-06-14 16:44:07','<div align=\"center\">\r\n<table width=\"686\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"182\"><b><i></i></b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"173\"><b>Order Items</b></td>\r\n<td width=\"331\"><b>Field Requirement </b><b>(optional)</b><b></b></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"182\"><b>orderkey</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"173\">Required on all follow up POSTs</td>\r\n<td width=\"331\">A valid order key</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"182\"></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"173\">Shipping values required to reach order-1 for first item</td>\r\n<td width=\"331\">Up to 1024 characters</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"182\"><b>item_&lt;n&gt;</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"173\">Key value for product model to be used to fulfill this item. Must be a valid</td>\r\n<td width=\"331\">A valid product key</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"182\"><b>item_&lt;n&gt;_set_copies</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"173\">Default 1. Sets the number of this item to print.</td>\r\n<td width=\"331\">[1-9][0-9]*</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"182\"><b>item_&lt;n&gt;_set_pref</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"173\">(opt) Partner reference information for this item. Holds a string that is accessible to the application when examining this order up to 1024 characters.</td>\r\n<td width=\"331\">Up to 1024 characters</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"182\"><b>item_&lt;n&gt;_set_note</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"173\">(opt) Note about this specific item up to 1024 characters.</td>\r\n<td width=\"331\">Up to 1024 characters</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"182\"><b>item_&lt;n&gt;_&lt;name&gt;</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"173\">Use this field name to upload a file or set text asset for item <b>n</b>s slot <b>name</b>. Some slots are optional. The names for slots are defined in the model.&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRepeat setting values or files to slot fields until all required fields are sent. There will be a error message for required slot which has been left empty slot</td>\r\n<td width=\"331\">A file of a acceptable mime type (currently only image/jpeg or image/png are accepted)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>','Order Items','','publish','closed','closed','','order-items','','','2013-06-17 11:53:11','2013-06-17 18:53:11','',41,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/angel-api-2/fields/order-items/',10,'page','',0),(48,1,'2013-06-14 09:44:07','2013-06-14 16:44:07','<div align=\"center\">\r\n<table width=\"520\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"116\"><b><i></i></b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"404\">Response Summary</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"116\"><b>orderkey</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"404\">Echoes back an orderkey on each step. It is created in the first and expected in all follow-ups. Without it a new order is started.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"116\"><b>order</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"404\">May contain place or ready in a POST. This field will return an error if any are present. It may return ready if there are no errors. If the order is ready and place was specified placed will be returned and the order will be completed.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>','Order Completion','','publish','closed','closed','','order-completion','','','2013-06-17 11:55:19','2013-06-17 18:55:19','',41,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/angel-api-2/fields/order-completion/',12,'page','',0),(49,1,'2013-06-14 09:44:07','2013-06-14 16:44:07','','Beginning an Order','','inherit','closed','closed','','46-revision','','','2013-06-14 09:44:07','2013-06-14 16:44:07','',46,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/46-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(50,1,'2013-06-14 09:44:07','2013-06-14 16:44:07','','Order Completion','','inherit','closed','closed','','48-revision','','','2013-06-14 09:44:07','2013-06-14 16:44:07','',48,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/48-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(51,1,'2013-06-14 09:45:23','2013-06-14 16:45:23','<div align=\"center\">\r\n<table width=\"699\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"163\"><b>debug</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"535\"><b>Any number of words from the following list separated by commas</b></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"163\"><b>Word</b><b></b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"535\">Meaning</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"163\"><b>order</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"535\">The entire order tree (valid or not) will be returned in the JSON item debug.order. This includes nested values for the complete order to this point.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>','Debug Options','','publish','closed','closed','','debug-options','','','2013-06-14 15:32:32','2013-06-14 22:32:32','',41,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/?page_id=51',11,'page','',0),(52,1,'2013-06-14 09:45:21','2013-06-14 16:45:21','','Debug Options','','inherit','closed','closed','','51-revision','','','2013-06-14 09:45:21','2013-06-14 16:45:21','',51,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/51-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(53,1,'2013-06-14 09:42:54','2013-06-14 16:42:54','','Responses','','inherit','closed','closed','','42-revision','','','2013-06-14 09:42:54','2013-06-14 16:42:54','',42,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/42-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(54,1,'2013-06-14 09:46:54','2013-06-14 16:46:54','','Responses','','inherit','closed','closed','','42-revision-2','','','2013-06-14 09:46:54','2013-06-14 16:46:54','',42,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/42-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(55,1,'2013-06-14 09:47:28','2013-06-14 16:47:28','Order requests may proceed in API steps or all of the needed information may be supplied in a single POST. Every step receives a response detailing the progress toward order-placement along with detail errors about items that prevent movement to the next step. This exchange requires two primary fields which need to be supplied in all POSTs and present in all responses as a progress indicator.\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"127\"><b>Parameter</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"559\"><b>Content</b></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"127\"><b>order</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"559\">May be POSTed as ready or place. The order will close and go live once all items are complete and place is given. If POSTed as ready the response will be ready to indicate that the order is ready to place or to take more items or changes.\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"116\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">** invalid</span></td>\r\n<td width=\"429\">This order doesnt have a Key yet. For example when theres a bad partnerkey.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"116\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">** incomplete</span></td>\r\n<td width=\"429\">This order has an orderkey but is Incomplete items are preventing it being ready.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"116\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">** ready</span></td>\r\n<td width=\"429\">This order is ready to be placed or changed some more.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"116\">placed<i></i></td>\r\n<td width=\"429\">A previous POST had order set to place and the contents were complete for all items. The order has been placed and is now closed to modification.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"127\"><b>partnerkey</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"559\">This is one of the partner keys created in your RPI Developer account. This only needs to be supplied at order-start. All other steps expect an orderkey. Indeed, it is considered an error to present both in the same POST.You may create and suspend any number of partner keys to control the applications you develop. By setting different keys for your separate products and even versions the keys allow you to independently disable your applications out in the field.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"127\"><b>orderkey</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"559\">This value is expected in all POSTs except the first. It is returned in every response except a failing mal-formed start which returned order ** none.Order keys are an added to enhance privacy for later communications about a specific order. They cannot be created, destroyed or suspended like other keys. They are only valid for modification up to 30 minutes after last change. If not completed by that time the order is disabled and garbage collected.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"127\"><b>item-<i>&lt;n&gt;</i></b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"559\">To create or change the model of an item in the order this value must present a model key. A model key must be supplied for each Item in an order. If the model key changes in later POSTs all the assets already assigned to that item are discarded.Model keys like partner keys are completely under the partners control. In the Partner Portal a partner may create and name a product model from any RPI supplied master model. Along with the partners defaulted content the new model can be given any number of keys.Here again the keys aim at controlling requests from the partners applications. This time in a finer per print product grain. For example a specific key with the note <i>version 1.2 of the iOS Ice Cruise Poster</i> could be enabled or disabled by the partner at any time.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"127\"><b>item-<i>&lt;n&gt;-&lt;slot&gt;</i></b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"559\">An asset for item ns product model. A model may require any number of named asset slots to be complete. Assets may be values or files. The &lt;n&gt; references the sequence or line item of an item number while &lt;slot&gt; is an asset name. Names are given to assets by the model attached to the model key for this item.In the Portal assets may be given default values by the partner as well as being set to required, optional or locked. Assets are supplied in a field are either directly in a text, or hidden field while a file field can be POSTed as part of a multipart/form-data. In-line text is may be supplied directly up to 1024 characters. Images and larger text should be uploaded as files.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>','All or Part','','publish','closed','closed','','all-or-part','','','2013-06-17 11:14:13','2013-06-17 18:14:13','',40,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/angel-api-2/structure/all-or-part/',0,'page','',0),(56,1,'2013-06-14 09:42:54','2013-06-14 16:42:54','','Keys and Security','','inherit','closed','closed','','43-revision','','','2013-06-14 09:42:54','2013-06-14 16:42:54','',43,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/43-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(57,1,'2013-06-14 09:48:40','2013-06-14 16:48:40','','Security Keys','','inherit','closed','closed','','43-revision-2','','','2013-06-14 09:48:40','2013-06-14 16:48:40','',43,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/43-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(58,1,'2013-06-14 09:50:19','2013-06-14 16:50:19','As a business partner you have been given access to RPIs Partner Portal. Within this portal you have the ability to create and enable/disable a number of partner keys. The intention is that you may attach these keys to different software versions, vending solutions, clients or groups. Each key records a note to aid you in identifying its purpose.\r\n\r\nWith any enabled partner key your agent or software can order a maximum value of RPI made goods. Through the Portal you can control this value as well as set a message associated with that key. The key tracks the value of orders placed against it.\r\n\r\nIf a message has been set in the key, that message will be returned to your application or client. As with all keys if the message begins with the flat \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">**</span> \" the key will be disabled and your message will be added to the error returned. For example a message of <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">** You must upgrade to version 2.0 of Vacation Dreams to continue</span> could be used along with app store code updates to distribute new keys inside an updated program.\r\n<h3><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Static Partner Keys are Dangerous</span></h3>\r\nThe <a href=\"/partner/web-api/examples/one-form/\">One Form</a> example given below harbors a major risk. While the server will insist on the transmission being encrypted (https) the Partner Key is openly readable if it is presented in a browser as this form might be. Indeed, multiple submissions of the form would trigger multiple original orders based on that single key. Any means which an abuser has of obtaining your Partner Key exposes us all to abuse.','Partner Keys','','publish','closed','closed','','partner-keys','','','2013-06-17 11:22:14','2013-06-17 18:22:14','',43,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/angel-api-2/security-keys/partner-keys/',8,'page','',0),(59,1,'2013-06-14 09:50:19','2013-06-14 16:50:19','Abuse is more difficult if the order were placed in steps. A simple protection makes use of the unique order key that is generated whenever a new order is begun. In an application or web-session alternative means of authorizing the transaction is often already available through payment or other accounting.\r\n\r\nIt is simple to let your server use the partner-key to obtain an order-key directly from the RPI order server. The order-key in that response can then be safely shared to complete a single order. It cannot be used to begin another nor can changes be confused with new orders.\r\n\r\nOrder-Keys are only valid for a period of time (currently a half-hour). Even with an Order-Key order contents wont change once the order is placed. (See tracking and cancellation etc. elsewhere.)','Order Keys','','publish','closed','closed','','order-keys','','','2013-06-17 11:25:36','2013-06-17 18:25:36','',43,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/angel-api-2/security-keys/order-keys/',10,'page','',0),(60,1,'2013-06-14 09:50:19','2013-06-14 16:50:19','Partners control which products are available under their keys. Product models are cloned from RPI-Master models. These models represent a physical RPI Product that may take a fixed set of content parts. These parts are placed in named slots. (Part A goes into Slot A)\r\n\r\nAfter a partner clones a model he gives it his own description and optionally fills some of the slots with assets. For example I might make three clones of the Poster with inset photo model. I could name them Sunset Cruise, Diving in Botny Bay and Dinner on Deck. By setting the background slot in each model to a photo appropriate to the description I can produce three products that only need their inset slots filled to be complete.\r\n\r\nThese models can be given any number of keys in the portal. These model keys can be distributed as desired among multiple applications or given to clients. Enabling and disabling the keys permits both automations and associates to know if a specific partner product is available to them at a specific time.','Model Keys','','publish','closed','closed','','model-keys','','','2013-06-14 15:21:59','2013-06-14 22:21:59','',43,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/angel-api-2/security-keys/model-keys/',11,'page','',0),(61,1,'2013-06-14 09:51:48','2013-06-14 16:51:48','If order is given a value of status the API will respond with ** incomplete or ready if the order is still being built. Once placed,printing,shipped andcancelled are later possible depending on the orders history. The responsetimed-outis only given for orders that did not complete within the time-out period. Note time-out orders cannot be resurrected. The information can be copied and a new order created.\r\n\r\nIn all cases a full set of detail about that order is available by specifying the <strong>debug </strong>parameter<strong>order</strong>. This will return a complete JSON structure dump of the existing order. For example:','Order Status','','publish','closed','closed','','order-status','','','2013-06-17 12:11:24','2013-06-17 19:11:24','',44,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/angel-api-2/status/order-status/',8,'page','',0),(62,1,'2013-06-14 09:51:48','2013-06-14 16:51:48','The API will also respond to an <strong>order</strong> of show. Within that request any number of <strong>model-&lt;n&gt;</strong> or<strong>group-&lt;n&gt;</strong>fields may be specified.\r\n\r\n<strong>model-&lt;n&gt;</strong> items expect a valid model key. An invalid response contains the Message as usual. If the key is valid the entire model structure is returned using the same <strong>model-&lt;n&gt;</strong>field name.\r\n\r\n<strong>group-&lt;n&gt;</strong> items expect a group name. A Partner\'s <a href=\"/partner/partner-account/product-groups/\">Product Groups</a>page allows the creation of a number of group names. Each name may be associated with any number of model keys. This field will return all of the currently active keys for that group name along with their notes and messages. Disabled keys will be omitted.','Model and Group Detail','','publish','closed','closed','','model-detail','','','2013-06-17 12:26:54','2013-06-17 19:26:54','',44,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/angel-api-2/status/model-detail/',10,'page','',0),(63,1,'2013-06-14 09:51:48','2013-06-14 16:51:48','This enhancement allows a partner to inquire which model keys are included in group &lt;gname&gt;. This is a convience management tool which allows an application to ask which product models belong to a group. Using this in an application may use the Angel API to dynamically create a list of possible offerings under control of the Portal.\r\n\r\nThe return will contain a JSON group with model keys as names and a full structure for each model as a value.','Model Groups','','publish','closed','closed','','model-groups','','','2013-06-14 15:35:45','2013-06-14 22:35:45','',44,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/angel-api-2/status/model-groups/',11,'