piprint.com/wp/?p=105',31,'nav_menu_item','',0),(106,1,'2013-06-14 09:46:57','2013-06-14 16:46:57','','Responses','','inherit','closed','closed','','42-revision-3','','','2013-06-14 09:46:57','2013-06-14 16:46:57','',42,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/42-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(107,1,'2013-06-14 10:10:06','2013-06-14 17:10:06','This API accepts requests as Posts only. All exchanges take place on a certificate encoded channel. To insure privacy all input are accepted in an https secured message body, not in the URL itself. Indeed, all action URLs POST to the same location. Currently that POST URL is: <a href=\"https://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/angel\">https://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/angel</a>. All attempted interaction with this URL which cannot be identified by the API will receive the simple two character response: no.\r\n\r\nTo simplify application development input to the API may be presented as JSON or as FORM encoded content of the POST. Data field names and types are the same in either form. In all cases the response will be in JSON. More concisely well formed POST can accept mime encodings of elither \"application/JSON\" or \"application/x-www-form-urlencoded\" for the parameters described here. Responses will always be \"application/JSON\".\r\n\r\nImages are accepted through form encoded file uploads. The actions of order-creation, order-item-addition, item-image-uploads and order-placement can be accomplished in one or more POSTS as convienent to the application. The only restriction is that not more that 30 minutes may elapse between order-creation and order-placement.','Transport and Encoding','','trash','closed','closed','','encoding','','','2013-06-17 11:11:27','2013-06-17 18:11:27','',40,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/?page_id=107',0,'page','',0),(108,1,'2013-06-14 10:10:04','2013-06-14 17:10:04','','Encoding','','inherit','closed','closed','','107-revision','','','2013-06-14 10:10:04','2013-06-14 17:10:04','',107,'http://