.com/wp/?p=173',13,'nav_menu_item','',0),(174,1,'2013-06-14 10:21:09','2013-06-14 17:21:09',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','174','','','2013-06-17 11:11:53','2013-06-17 18:11:53','',44,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/?p=174',14,'nav_menu_item','',0),(175,1,'2013-06-14 10:21:09','2013-06-14 17:21:09',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','175','','','2013-06-17 11:11:53','2013-06-17 18:11:53','',44,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/?p=175',15,'nav_menu_item','',0),(176,1,'2013-06-14 10:21:09','2013-06-14 17:21:09',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','176','','','2013-06-17 11:11:53','2013-06-17 18:11:53','',44,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/?p=176',16,'nav_menu_item','',0),(259,1,'2013-06-14 15:19:41','2013-06-14 22:19:41','<p class=\"MsoNormal\">This API accepts requests as Posts only. All exchanges take place on a certificate encoded channel. To insure privacy all input are accepted in an https secured message body, not in the URL itself. Indeed, all action URLs POST to the same location. Currently that POST URL is: <a href=\"https://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/angel\">https://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/angel</a>. All attempted interaction with this URL which cannot be identified by the API will receive the simple two character response: no.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">To simplify application development input to the API may be presented as JSON or as FORM encoded content of the POST. Data field names and types are the same in either form. In all cases the response will be in JSON. More concisely well formed POST can accept mime encodings of elither \"application/JSON\" or \"application/x-www-form-urlencoded\" for the parameters described here. Responses will always be \"application/JSON\".</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Images are accepted through form encoded file uploads. The actions of order-creation, order-item-addition, item-image-uploads and order-placement can be accomplished in one or more POSTS as convienent to the application. The only restriction is that not more that 30 minutes may elapse between order-creation and order-placement.</p>','Structure','','inherit','closed','closed','','40-revision-10','','','2013-06-14 15:19:41','2013-06-14 22:19:41','',40,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/partner/40-revision-10/',0,'revision','',0),(263,1,'2013-06-14 13:14:08','2013-06-14 20:14:08','Order requests may proceed in API steps or all of the needed information may be supplied in a single POST. Every step receives a response detailing the progress toward order-placement along with detail errors about items that prevent movement to the next step. This exchange requires two primary fields which need to be supplied in all POSTs and present in all responses as a progress indicator.\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"127\"><b>Parameter</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"559\"><b>Content</b></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"127\"><b>order</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"559\">May be POSTed as ready or place. The order will close and go live once all items are complete and place is given. If POSTed as ready the response will be ready to indicate that the order is ready to place or to take more items or changes.\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"116\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">** invalid</span></td>\r\n<td width=\"429\">This order doesnt have a Key yet. For example when theres a bad partnerkey.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"116\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">** incomplete</span></td>\r\n<td width=\"429\">This order has an orderkey but is Incomplete items are preventing it being ready.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"116\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">** ready</span></td>\r\n<td width=\"429\">This order is ready to be placed or changed some more.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"116\">placed<i></i></td>\r\n<td width=\"429\">A previous POST had order set to placed and the contents were complete for all items. The order has been placed and is now closed to modification.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"127\"><b>partnerkey</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"559\">This is one of the partner keys created in your RPI Developer account. This only needs to be supplied at order-start. All other steps expect an orderkey. Indeed, it is considered an error to present both in the same POST.You may create and suspend any number of partner keys to control the applications you develop. By setting different keys for your separate products and even versions the keys allow you to independently disable your applications out in the field.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"127\"><b>orderkey</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"559\">This value is expected in all POSTs except the first. It is returned in every response except a failing mal-formed start which returned order ** none.Order keys are an added to enhance privacy for later communications about a specific order. They cannot be created, destroyed or suspended like other keys. They are only valid for modification up to 30 minutes after last change. If not completed by that time the order is disabled and garbage collected.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"127\"><b>item-<i>&lt;n&gt;</i></b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"559\">To create or change the model of an item in the order this value must present a model key. A model key must be supplied for each Item in an order. If the model key changes in later POSTs all the assets already assigned to that item are discarded.Model keys like partner keys are completely under the partners control. In the Partner Portal a partner may create and name a product model from any RPI supplied master model. Along with the partners defaulted content the new model can be given any number of keys.\r\n\r\nHere again the keys aim at controlling requests from the partners applications. This time in a finer per print product grain. For example a specific key with the note <i>version 1.2 of the iOS Ice Cruise Poster</i> could be enabled or disabled by the partner at any time.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"127\"><b>item-<i>&lt;n&gt;-&lt;slot&gt;</i></b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"559\">An asset for item ns product model. A model may require any number of named asset slots to be complete. Assets may be values or files. The &lt;n&gt; references the sequence or line item of an item number while &lt;slot&gt; is an asset name. Names are given to assets by the model attached to the model key for this item.In the Portal assets may be given default values by the partner as well as being set to required, optional or locked. Assets are supplied in a field are either directly in a text, or hidden field while a file field can be POSTed as part of a multipart/form-data. In-line text is may be supplied directly up to 1024 characters. Images and larger text should be uploaded as files.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>','All or Part','','inherit','closed','closed','','55-revision-3','','','2013-06-14 13:14:08','2013-06-14 20:14:08','',55,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/partner/55-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(177,1,'2013-06-14 10:24:26','2013-06-14 17:24:26',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','177','','','2013-06-17 13:46:48','2013-06-17 20:46:48','',9,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/?p=177',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(178,1,'2013-06-14 10:24:26','2013-06-14 17:24:26',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','178','','','2013-06-17 13:46:48','2013-06-17 20:46:48','',9,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/?p=178',4,'nav_menu_item','',0),(179,1,'2013-06-14 10:24:26','2013-06-14 17:24:26',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','179','','','2013-06-17 13:46:48','2013-06-17 20:46:48','',9,'http://storefronttest.rpi