time the order is disabled and garbage collected.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"127\"><b>item-<i>&lt;n&gt;</i></b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"559\">To create or change the model of an item in the order this value must present a model key. A model key must be supplied for each Item in an order. If the model key changes in later POSTs all the assets already assigned to that item are discarded.\r\n\r\nModel keys like partner keys are completely under the partners control. In the Partner Portal a partner may create and name a product model from any RPI supplied master model. Along with the partners defaulted content the new model can be given any number of keys.\r\n\r\nHere again the keys aim at controlling requests from the partners applications. This time in a finer per print product grain. For example a specific key with the note <i>version 1.2 of the iOS Ice Cruise Poster</i> could be enabled or disabled by the partner at any time.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"127\"><b>item-<i>&lt;n&gt;-&lt;slot&gt;</i></b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"559\">An asset for item ns product model. A model may require any number of named asset slots to be complete. Assets may be values or files. The &lt;n&gt; references the sequence or line item of an item number while &lt;slot&gt; is an asset name. Names are given to assets by the model attached to the model key for this item.\r\n\r\nIn the Portal assets may be given default values by the partner as well as being set to required, optional or locked. Assets are supplied in a field are either directly in a text, or hidden field while a file field can be POSTed as part of a multipart/form-data. In-line text is may be supplied directly up to 1024 characters. Images and larger text should be uploaded as files.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>','All or Part','','inherit','closed','closed','','55-revision-2','','','2013-06-14 10:15:52','2013-06-14 17:15:52','',55,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/w