;\">=</span><span style=\"color: #e60000;\">\"submit\"</span><span style=\"color: #074726;\">name</span><span style=\"color: #806030;\">=</span><span style=\"color: #e60000;\">\"do\"</span><span style=\"color: #074726;\">value</span><span style=\"color: #806030;\">=</span><span style=\"color: #e60000;\">\"Submit\"</span><span style=\"color: #a65700;\">&gt;</span>\r\n  <span style=\"color: #a65700;\">&lt;/</span><span style=\"color: #400000; font-weight: bold;\">form</span><span style=\"color: #a65700;\">&gt;</span>\r\n<span style=\"color: #a65700;\">&lt;/</span><span style=\"color: #400000; font-weight: bold;\">body</span><span style=\"color: #a65700;\">&gt;</span></pre>','Two of Two','','publish','closed','closed','','two-of-two','','','2013-06-14 15:55:50','2013-06-14 22:55:50','',211,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/two-of-two/',6,'page','',0),(215,1,'2013-06-14 15:18:19','2013-06-14 22:18:19','','One Form','','inherit','closed','closed','','212-revision','','','2013-06-14 15:18:19','2013-06-14 22:18:19','',212,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/212-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(216,1,'2013-06-14 15:18:19','2013-06-14 22:18:19','','One of Two','','inherit','closed','closed','','213-revision','','','2013-06-14 15:18:19','2013-06-14 22:18:19','',213,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/213-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(217,1,'2013-06-14 15:18:19','2013-06-14 22:18:19','','Two of Two','','inherit','closed','closed','','214-revision','','','2013-06-14 15:18:19','2013-06-14 22:18:19','',214,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/214-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(218,1,'2013-06-14 15:18:33','2013-06-14 22:18:33','','Two of Two','','inherit','closed','closed','','214-revision-2','','','2013-06-14 15:18:33','2013-06-14 22:18:33','',214,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/214-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(219,1,'2013-06-14 15:18:27','2013-06-14 22:18:27','','One Form','','inherit','closed','closed','','212-revision-2','','','2013-06-14 15:18:27','2013-06-14 22:18:27','',212,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/212-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(220,1,'2013-06-14 15:18:19','2013-06-14 22:18:19','','Examples','','inherit','closed','closed','','211-revision','','','2013-06-14 15:18:19','2013-06-14 22:18:19','',211,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/211-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(266,1,'2013-06-17 11:16:06','2013-06-17 18:16:06','Once an order is accepted real goods and services will be expended to create and ship the result. The authorization that allows this is a potential point of abuse. RPI supplies several tools and checks which can help you to manage your authority and applications which use these services.\r\n\r\nRPI provides unique keys to help you control the applications you are running as well as the applications and product models you are developing. These keys always refer to a specific Partner, Product Model or Order. They are generated in a way that guarantees they are unique and at the same time not reasonably guessable.\r\n\r\nBy controlling which customers and applications are given which keys you can remain in control of each item separately. Giving applications different Model keys for the same product allows you to disable that product in a specific application without affecting you other commerce. Attaching partner unique partner keys to a version of an application provides a way to disable that specific version in the field and provide a message or action to the application. Only order keys are one-to-one. An order key is the only valid way to continue, cancel or check on a order in progress.','Security Keys','','inherit','closed','closed','','43-revision-10','','','2013-06-17 11:16:06','2013-06-17 18:16:06','',43,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/partner/43-revision-10/',0,'revision','',0),(221,1,'2013-06-14 15:05:47','2013-06-14 22:05:47','<p class=\"MsoNormal\">This API accepts requests as Posts only. All exchanges take place on a certificate encoded channel. To insure privacy all input are accepted in an https secured message body, not in the URL itself. Indeed, all action URLs POST to the same location. Currently that POST URL is: <a href=\"https://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/angel\">https://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/angel</a>. All attempted interaction with this URL which cannot be identified by the API will receive the simple two character response: no.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">To simplify application development input to the API may be presented as JSON or as FORM encoded content of the POST. Data field names and types are the same in either form. In all cases the response will be in JSON. More concisely well formed POST can accept mime encodings of elither \"application/JSON\" or \"application/x-www-form-urlencoded\" for the parameters described here. Responses will always be \"application/JSON\".</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Images are accepted through form encoded file uploads. The actions of order-creation, order-item-addition, item-image-uploads and order-placement can be accomplished in one or more POSTS as convienent to the application. The only restriction is that not more that 30 minutes may elapse between order-creation and order-placement.</p>','Structure','','inherit','closed','closed','','40-revision-9','','','2013-06-14 15:05:47','2013-06-14 22:05:47','',40,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/40-revision-9/',0,'revision','',0),(222,1,'2013-06-14 15:16:03','2013-06-14 22:16:03','Once an order is accepted real goods and services will be expended to create and ship the result. The authorization that allows this is a potential point of abuse. RPI supplies several tools and checks which can help you to manage your authority and applications which use these services.\r\n\r\nRPI provides unique keys to help you control the applications you are running as well as the applications and product models you are developing. These keys always refer to a specific Partner, Product Model or Order. They are generated in a way that guarantees they are unique and at the same time the are not reasonably guessable.\r\n\r\nBy controlling which customers and applications are given which keys you can remain in control of each item separately. Giving applications different Model keys for the same product allows you to disable that product in a specific application without affecting you other commerce. Attaching partner unique partner keys to a version of an application provides a way to disable that specific version in the field and provide a message or action to the application. Only order keys are one-to-one. An order key is the only valid way to continue, cancel or check on a order in progress.','Security Keys','','inherit','closed','closed','','43-revision-8','','','2013-06-14 15:16:03','2013-06-14 22:16:03','',43,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/43-revision-8/',0,'revision','',0),(223,1,'2013-06-14 15:03:17','2013-06-14 22:03:17','','Fields','','inherit','closed','closed','','41-revision-2','','','2013-06-14 15:03:17','2013-06-14 22:03:17','',41,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/41-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(224,1,'2013-06-14 15:03:21','2013-06-14 22:03:21','','Status','','inherit','closed','closed','','44-revision-2','','','2013-06-14 15:03:21','2013-06-14 22:03:21','',44,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/44-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(225,1,'2013-06-14 09:50:19','2013-06-14 16:50:19','','Order Keys','','inherit','closed','closed','','59-revision','','','2013-06-14 09:50:19','2013-06-14 16:50:19','',59,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/59-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(226,1,'2013-06-14 09:50:19','2013-06-14 16:50:19','','Model Keys','','inherit','closed','closed','','60-revision','','','2013-06-14 09:50:19','2013-06-14 16:50:19','',60,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/60-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(227,1,'2013-06-17 11:45:08','2013-06-17 18:45:08','The default data encoding used by order submission is exactly the same encoding used in HTML POST forms. This allows a large amount of data to be securely encrypted and delivered to the server in one large or many small steps. A standard browser delivers <strong>multipart/form-data</strong>when POSTing forms and always when doing file-uploads.\n\nAs the HTML examples show it is straight forward to drive the order interface directly from a browser session. Most application building environments provide the means to construct the POST information directly.\n\nThe naming conventions used in this API are aimed at allowing a flat list of names to form the hierarchy needed to express an order with multiple items each of which may require multiple assets to personalize the result. There are no upper case letters in any field name. Field names are qualified beginning with words separated by a  \'_\' (under bar not a \'-\', dash) from the root name. These qualifi allows different portions of the order to be addressed without the use of container elements. ','Fields','','inherit','closed','closed','','41-autosave','','','2013-06-17 11:45:08','2013-06-17 18:45:08','',41,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/41-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(228,1,'2013-06-14 15:20:01','2013-06-14 22:20:01','','Fields','','inherit','closed','closed','','41-revision-3','','','2013-06-14 15:20:01','2013-06-14 22:20:01','',41,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/41-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(229,1,'2013-06-14 09:44:09','2013-06-14 16:44:09','','Beginning an Order','','inherit','closed','closed','','46-revision-2','','','2013-06-14 09:44:09','2013-06-14 16:44:09','',46,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/46-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(230,1,'2013-06-14 09:44:07','2013-06-14 16:44:07','','Order Items','','inherit','closed','closed','','47-revision','','','2013-06-14 09:44:07','2013-06-14 16:44:07','',47,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/47-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(231,1,'2013-06-14 09:45:23','2013-06-14 16:45:23','','Debug Options','','inherit','closed','closed','','51-revision-2','','','2013-06-14 09:45:23','2013-06-14 16:45:23','',51,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/51-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(232,1,'2013-06-14 09:45:21','2013-06-14 16:45:21','','Order Completion','','inherit','closed','closed','','48-revision-2','','','2013-06-14 09:45:21','2013-06-14 16:45:21','',48,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/48-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(233,1,'2013-06-14 15:07:16','2013-06-14 22:07:16','The error messages summarize and complain about fields under their field-names in a JSON response. Every item causing a problem will start the response with ** . If a non-error response is called for it will not begin ** .\r\n\r\nErrors may provide more detail. The message will contain none, missing, invalid, or incomplete following the initial **. Detail information will follow the summary word with a : , separator. Heres an example where a file field was sent with no file content.\r\n<pre>{</pre>\r\n<pre><b>order</b>:\"** incomplete\",</pre>\r\n<pre><b>orderkey</b>:\"RA98C1876O8D170EA3296B215BB263CFADBA23AD12\",</pre>\r\n<pre><b>item-1-inset</b>:\"** missing: ** Upload failed UPLOAD_ERR_NO_FILE\"</pre>\r\n<pre>}</pre>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Responses','','inherit','closed','closed','','42-revision-5','','','2013-06-14 15:07:16','2013-06-14 22:07:16','',42,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/42-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(234,1,'2013-06-14 09:51:50','2013-06-14 16:51:50','','Order Status','','inherit','closed','closed','','61-revision-2','','','2013-06-14 09:51:50','2013-06-14 16:51:50','',61,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/61-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(235,1,'2013-06-14 09:51:48','2013-06-14 16:51:48','','Model Detail','','inherit','closed','closed','','62-revision','','','2013-06-14 09:51:48','2013-06-14 16:51:48','',62,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/62-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(236,1,'2013-06-14 09:51:48','2013-06-14 16:51:48','','Model Groups','','inherit','closed','closed','','63-revision','','','2013-06-14 09:51:48','2013-06-14 16:51:48','',63,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/63-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(237,1,'2013-06-14 15:19:07','2013-06-14 22:19:07','','Examples','','inherit','closed','closed','','211-revision-2','','','2013-06-14 15:19:07','2013-06-14 22:19:07','',211,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/211-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(238,1,'2013-06-14 15:18:40','2013-06-14 22:18:40','','One Form','','inherit','closed','closed','','212-revision-3','','','2013-06-14 15:18:40','2013-06-14 22:18:40','',212,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/212-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(239,1,'2013-06-14 15:37:38','2013-06-14 22:37:38','&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\"&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;title&gt;Order in a single POST&lt;/title&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;/head&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;body&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;form action=\"http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/orderup/\" method=\"POST\" enctype=\"multipart/form-data\"&gt;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&lt;!-- Every new order needs a valid partner key. --&gt;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\npartnerkey:\r\n\r\n&lt;input size=\"60\" type=\"text\" name=\"partnerkey\" value=\"RA98C18E2PE36D3C4B419C1190710045F5F1526D23\"&gt;&lt;br&gt;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&lt;!-- Fields for the first item --&gt;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nitem-1:\r\n\r\n&lt;input size=\"60\" type=\"text\" name=\"item-1\" value=\"RA98C18A9ME93F04DDE4DF348EBE142008876BF5BD\"&gt;&lt;br&gt;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&lt;!-- This field may be omitted if only one copy is wanted. In this\r\n\r\ncase we want 2. --&gt;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nitem-1-set-copies:\r\n\r\n&lt;input size=\"60\" type=\"text\" name=\"item-1-copies\" value=\"2\"&gt;&lt;br&gt;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&lt;!-- This model has slots for a background and an inset. The\r\n\r\nbackground is defaulted in the model so only the inset is\r\n\r\nmanditory. --&gt;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nitem-1-inset:\r\n\r\n&lt;input size=\"60\" type=\"file\" name=\"item-1-inset