\'>value</span><span style=\'color:#806030; \'>=</span><span style=\'color:#e60000; \'>\"USA\"</span><span style=\'color:#a65700; \'>></span><span style=\'color:#a65700; \'>&lt;</span><span style=\'color:#400000; font-weight:bold; \'>br</span><span style=\'color:#074726; \'> </span><span style=\'color:#a65700; \'>/></span>\r\n\r\n    <span style=\'color:#c34e00; \'>&lt;!-- To double check debug is asking that the entire order be</span>\r\n<span style=\'color:#c34e00; \'>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;echoed back. --></span>\r\n\r\ndebug:\r\n    <span style=\'color:#a65700; \'>&lt;</span><span style=\'color:#400000; font-weight:bold; \'>input</span><span style=\'color:#074726; \'> </span><span style=\'color:#074726; \'>size</span><span style=\'color:#806030; \'>=</span><span style=\'color:#e60000; \'>\"60\"</span><span style=\'color:#074726; \'> </span><span style=\'color:#074726; \'>type</span><span style=\'color:#806030; \'>=</span><span style=\'color:#e60000; \'>\"text\"</span><span style=\'color:#074726; \'></span>\r\n<span style=\'color:#074726; \'>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;</span><span style=\'color:#074726; \'>name</span><span style=\'color:#806030; \'>=</span><span style=\'color:#e60000; \'>\"debug\"</span><span style=\'color:#074726; \'> </span><span style=\'color:#074726; \'>value</span><span style=\'color:#806030; \'>=</span><span style=\'color:#e60000; \'>\"order\"</span><span style=\'color:#a65700; \'>></span><span style=\'color:#a65700; \'>&lt;</span><span style=\'color:#400000; font-weight:bold; \'>br</span><span style=\'color:#074726; \'> </span><span style=\'color:#a65700; \'>/></span>\r\n\r\n    <span style=\'color:#c34e00; \'>&lt;!-- We\'re really good so without even checking let\'s place the</span>\r\n<span style=\'color:#c34e00; \'>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;order. Note any invalid input will cause an error return. Only a</span>\r\n<span style=\'color:#c34e00; \'>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;totally viable order will return \'placed\'. --></span>\r\n\r\norder:\r\n    <span style=\'color:#a65700; \'>&lt;</span><span style=\'color:#400000; font-weight:bold; \'>input</span><span style=\'color:#074726; \'> </span><span style=\'color:#074726; \'>size</span><span style=\'color:#806030; \'>=</span><span style=\'color:#e60000; \'>\"60\"</span><span style=\'color:#074726; \'> </span><span style=\'color:#074726; \'>type</span><span style=\'color:#806030; \'>=</span><span style=\'color:#e60000; \'>\"text\"</span><span style=\'color:#074726; \'></span>\r\n<span style=\'color:#074726; \'>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;</span><span style=\'color:#074726; \'>name</span><span style=\'color:#806030; \'>=</span><span style=\'color:#e60000; \'>\"order\"</span><span style=\'color:#074726; \'> </span><span style=\'color:#074726; \'>value</span><span style=\'color:#806030; \'>=</span><span style=\'color:#e60000; \'>\"place\"</span><span style=\'color:#a65700; \'>></span><span style=\'color:#a65700; \'>&lt;</span><span style=\'color:#400000; font-weight:bold; \'>br</span><span style=\'color:#074726; \'> </span><span style=\'color:#a65700; \'>/></span>\r\n\r\n    <span style=\'color:#a65700; \'>&lt;</span><span style=\'color:#400000; font-weight:bold; \'>input</span><span style=\'color:#074726; \'> </span><span style=\'color:#074726; \'>type</span><span style=\'color:#806030; \'>=</span><span style=\'color:#e60000; \'>\"submit\"</span><span style=\'color:#074726; \'> </span><span style=\'color:#074726; \'>name</span><span style=\'color:#806030; \'>=</span><span style=\'color:#e60000; \'>\"do\"</span><span style=\'color:#074726; \'> </span><span style=\'color:#074726; \'>value</span><span style=\'color:#806030; \'>=</span><span style=\'color:#e60000; \'>\"Submit\"</span><span style=\'color:#a65700; \'>></span>\r\n  <span style=\'color:#a65700; \'>&lt;/</span><span style=\'color:#400000; font-weight:bold; \'>form</span><span style=\'color:#a65700; \'>></span>\r\n<span style=\'color:#a65700; \'>&lt;/</span><span style=\'color:#400000; font-weight:bold; \'>body</span><span style=\'color:#a65700; \'>></span>\r\n</pre>','Two of Two','','inherit','closed','closed','','214-revision-4','','','2013-06-14 15:55:32','2013-06-14 22:55:32','',214,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/wp/214-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(260,1,'2013-06-17 11:09:15','2013-06-17 18:09:15','<p class=\"MsoNormal\">This API accepts requests as Posts only. All exchanges take place on a certificate encoded channel. To insure privacy all input are accepted in an https secured message body, not in the URL itself. Indeed, all action URLs POST to the same location. Currently that POST URL is: <a href=\"https://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/orderup\">https://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/orderup</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">To application input to the API may be presented as JSON or as FORM encoded content of a POST. Data field names and types are the same in either form. In all cases the response will be in JSON. More concisely a well formed POST can accept mime encodings of either \"application/JSON\" or \"multipart/form-data\" for the parameters described here. Responses will always be \"application/JSON\".</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Images are typically accepted through form encoded file uploads. The actions of order-creation, order-item-addition, item-image-uploads and order-placement can be accomplished in one or more POSTS as convienent to the application. The only restriction is that not more that 30 minutes may elapse between order-creation and order-placement.</p>','Structure','','inherit','closed','closed','','40-autosave','','','2013-06-17 11:09:15','2013-06-17 18:09:15','',40,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/partner/40-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(261,1,'2013-06-17 11:04:24','2013-06-17 18:04:24','<p class=\"MsoNormal\">This API accepts requests as Posts only. All exchanges take place on a certificate encoded channel. To insure privacy all input are accepted in an https secured message body, not in the URL itself. Indeed, all action URLs POST to the same location. Currently that POST URL is: <a href=\"https://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/orderup\">https://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/orderup</a>. All attempted interaction with this URL which cannot be identified by the API will receive the simple two character response: no.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">To simplify application development input to the API may be presented as JSON or as FORM encoded content of the POST. Data field names and types are the same in either form. In all cases the response will be in JSON. More concisely well formed POST can accept mime encodings of elither \"application/JSON\" or \"application/x-www-form-urlencoded\" for the parameters described here. Responses will always be \"application/JSON\".</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Images are accepted through form encoded file uploads. The actions of order-creation, order-item-addition, item-image-uploads and order-placement can be accomplished in one or more POSTS as convienent to the application. The only restriction is that not more that 30 minutes may elapse between order-creation and order-placement.</p>','Structure','','inherit','closed','closed','','40-revision-11','','','2013-06-17 11:04:24','2013-06-17 18:04:24','',40,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/partner/40-revision-11/',0,'revision','',0),(264,1,'2013-06-17 11:13:28','2013-06-17 18:13:28','Order requests may proceed in API steps or all of the needed information may be supplied in a single POST. Every step receives a response detailing the progress toward order-placement along with detail errors about items that prevent movement to the next step. This exchange requires two primary fields which need to be supplied in all POSTs and present in all responses as a progress indicator.\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"127\"><b>Parameter</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"559\"><b>Content</b></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"127\"><b>order</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"559\">May be POSTed as ready or place. The order will close and go live once all items are complete and place is given. If POSTed as ready the response will be ready to indicate that the order is ready to place or to take more items or changes.\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"116\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">** invalid</span></td>\r\n<td width=\"429\">This order doesnt have a Key yet. For example when theres a bad partnerkey.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"116\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">** incomplete</span></td>\r\n<td width=\"429\">This order has an orderkey but is Incomplete items are preventing it being ready.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"116\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">** ready</span></td>\r\n<td width=\"429\">This order is ready to be placed or changed some more.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"116\">placed<i></i></td>\r\n<td width=\"429\">A previous POST had order set to place and the contents were complete for all items. The order has been placed and is now closed to modification.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"127\"><b>partnerkey</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"559\">This is one of the partner keys created in your RPI Developer account. This only needs to be supplied at order-start. All other steps expect an orderkey. Indeed, it is considered an error to present both in the same POST.You may create and suspend any number of partner keys to control the applications you develop. By setting different keys for your separate products and even versions the keys allow you to independently disable your applications out in the field.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"127\"><b>orderkey</b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"559\">This value is expected in all POSTs except the first. It is returned in every response except a failing mal-formed start which returned order ** none.Order keys are an added to enhance privacy for later communications about a specific order. They cannot be created, destroyed or suspended like other keys. They are only valid for modification up to 30 minutes after last change. If not completed by that time the order is disabled and garbage collected.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"127\"><b>item-<i>&lt;n&gt;</i></b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"559\">To create or change the model of an item in the order this value must present a model key. A model key must be supplied for each Item in an order. If the model key changes in later POSTs all the assets already assigned to that item are discarded.Model keys like partner keys are completely under the partners control. In the Partner Portal a partner may create and name a product model from any RPI supplied master model. Along with the partners defaulted content the new model can be given any number of keys.Here again the keys aim at controlling requests from the partners applications. This time in a finer per print product grain. For example a specific key with the note <i>version 1.2 of the iOS Ice Cruise Poster</i> could be enabled or disabled by the partner at any time.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"127\"><b>item-<i>&lt;n&gt;-&lt;slot&gt;</i></b></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"559\">An asset for item ns product model. A model may require any number of named asset slots to be complete. Assets may be values or files. The &lt;n&gt; references the sequence or line item of an item number while &lt;slot&gt; is an asset name. Names are given to assets by the model attached to the model key for this item.In the Portal assets may be given default values by the partner as well as being set to required, optional or locked. Assets are supplied in a field are either directly in a text, or hidden field while a file field can be POSTed as part of a multipart/form-data. In-line text is may be supplied directly up to 1024 characters. Images and larger text should be uploaded as files.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>','All or Part','','inherit','closed','closed','','55-revision-4','','','2013-06-17 11:13:28','2013-06-17 18:13:28','',55,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/partner/55-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(265,1,'2013-06-14 15:19:45','2013-06-14 22:19:45','Once an order is accepted real goods and services will be expended to create and ship the result. The authorization that allows this is a potential point of abuse. RPI supplies several tools and checks which can help you to manage your authority and applications which use these services.\r\n\r\nRPI provides unique keys to help you control the applications you are running as well as the applications and product models you are developing. These keys always refer to a specific Partner, Product Model or Order. They are generated in a way that guarantees they are unique and at the same time the are not reasonably guessable.\r\n\r\nBy controlling which customers and applications are given which keys you can remain in control of each item separately. Giving applications different Model keys for the same product allows you to disable that product in a specific application without affecting you other commerce. Attaching partner unique partner keys to a version of an application provides a way to disable that specific version in the field and provide a message or action to the application. Only order keys are one-to-one. An order key is the only valid way to continue, cancel or check on a order in progress.','Security Keys','','inherit','closed','closed','','43-revision-9','','','2013-06-14 15:19:45','2013-06-14 22:19:45','',43,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/partner/43-revision-9/',0,'revision','',0),(267,1,'2013-06-17 11:21:02','2013-06-17 18:21:02','As a business partner you have been given access to RPIs Partner Portal. Within this portal you have the ability to create and enable/disable a number of partner keys. The intention is that you may attach these keys to different software versions, vending solutions, clients or groups. Each key records a note to aid you in identifying its purpose.\n\nWith any enabled partner key your agent or software can order a maximum value of RPI made goods. Through the Portal you can control this value as well as set a message associated with that key. The key tracks the value of orders placed against it.\n\nIf a message has been set in the key, that message will be returned to your application or client. As with all keys if the message begins with the flat \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">**</span> \" the key will be disabled and your message will be added to the error returned. For example a message of <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">** You must upgrade to version 2.0 of Vacation Dreams to continue</span> could be used along with app store code updates to distribute new keys inside an updated program.\n<h3><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Static Partner Keys are Dangerous</span></h3>\nThe <a href=\"file:///C:/Users/grant.tegtmeier/Documents/storefront/Web%20API%200.3.docx#_HTML_in_One\">One Form</a> example given below harbors a major risk. While the server will insist on the transmission being encrypted (https) the Partner Key is openly readable if it is presented in a browser as this form might be. Indeed, multiple submissions of the form would trigger multiple original orders based on that single key. Any means which an abuser has of obtaining your Partner Key exposes us all to abuse.','Partner Keys','','inherit','closed','closed','','58-autosave','','','2013-06-17 11:21:02','2013-06-17 18:21:02','',58,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/partner/58-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(268,1,'2013-06-14 15:16:48','2013-06-14 22:16:48','As a business partner you have been given access to RPIs Partner Portal. Within this portal you have the ability to create and enable/disable a number of partner keys. The intention is that you may attach these keys to different software versions, vending solutions, clients or groups. Each key records a note to aid you in identifying its purpose.\r\n\r\nWith any enabled partner key your agent or software can order a maximum value of RPI made goods. Through the Portal you can control this value as well as set a message associated with that key. The key tracks the value of orders placed against it.\r\n\r\nSetting the value to 0 (or less that the accrued amount) will disable the key. If a message has been set in the key, that message will be returned to your application or client as the reason for the error. For example a message of You must upgrade to version 2.0 of Vacation Dreams to continue could be used along with app store code updates to distribute new keys inside an updated program.\r\n<h3><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Static Partner Keys are Dangerous</span></h3>\r\nThe <a href=\"file:///C:/Users/grant.tegtmeier/Documents/storefront/Web%20API%200.3.docx#_HTML_in_One\">One Form</a> example given below harbors a major risk. While the server will insist on the transmission being encrypted (https) the Partner Key is openly readable if it is presented in a browser as this form might be. Indeed, multiple submissions of the form would trigger multiple original orders based on that single key. Any means which an abuser has of obtaining your Partner Key exposes us all to abuse.','Partner Keys','','inherit','closed','closed','','58-revision-2','','','2013-06-14 15:16:48','2013-06-14 22:16:48','',58,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/partner/58-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(269,1,'2013-06-17 11:25:20','2013-06-17 18:25:20','Abuse is more difficult if the order were placed in steps. A simple protection makes use of the unique order key that is generated whenever a new order is begun. In an application or web-session alternative means of authorizing the transaction is often already available through payment or other accounting.\n\nIt is simple to let your server use the partner-key to obtain an order-key directly from the RPI order server. The order-key in that response can then be safely shared to complete a single order. It cannot be used to begin another nor can changes be confused with new orders.\n\nOrder-Keys are only valid for a period of time (currently a half-hour). Even with an Order-Key order contents wont change once the order is placed. (See tracking and cancelation etc. elsewhere.)','Order Keys','','inherit','closed','closed','','59-autosave','','','2013-06-17 11:25:20','2013-06-17 18:25:20','',59,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/partner/59-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(270,1,'2013-06-14 15:21:27','2013-06-14 22:21:27','Abuse is more difficult if the order were placed in steps. A simple protection makes use of the unique order key that is generated whenever the order-start stage has completed. In an application or web-session alternative means of authorizing the transaction is often already available through payment or other accounting.\r\n\r\nIt is simple to let your server obtain an order-key by having it echo the customer and shipping info to the RPI server. The order-key in that response can then be safely shared to complete the order. It cannot be used to begin another.\r\n\r\nOrder-Keys are only valid for a period of time (currently a half-hour). Even with an Order-Key order contents wont change once the order is placed. (See tracking and cancelation etc. elsewhere.)','Order Keys','','inherit','closed','closed','','59-revision-2','','','2013-06-14 15:21:27','2013-06-14 22:21:27','',59,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/partner/59-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(271,1,'2013-06-14 15:31:01','2013-06-14 22:31:01','The default data encoding used by order submission is exactly the same encoding used in HTML POST forms. This allow a large amount of data to be securely encrypted and delivered to the server in one large or many small steps. Browsers standardly deliver <strong>multipart/form-data</strong>in forms and always when doing file uploads.\r\n\r\nAs the examples show it is straight forward to drive the order interface directly from a browser session. Most application building environments provide the means to construct these POSTs simply.\r\n\r\nMost of the naming conventions used in this API are aimed at allowing a flat list of names to form the hierarchy needed to express an order with multiple items each of which may require multiple assets to personalize the result.','Fields','','inherit','closed','closed','','41-revision-4','','','2013-06-14 15:31:01','2013-06-14 22:31:01','',41,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/partner/41-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(272,1,'2013-06-17 11:38:37','2013-06-17 18:38:37','The default data encoding used by order submission is exactly the same encoding used in HTML POST forms. This allows a large amount of data to be securely encrypted and delivered to the server in one large or many small steps. A standard browser delivers <strong>multipart/form-data</strong>when POSTing forms and always when doing file-uploads.\r\n\r\nAs the HTML examples show it is straight forward to drive the order interface directly from a browser session. Most application building environments provide the means to construct the POST information directly.\r\n\r\nThe naming conventions used in this API are aimed at allowing a flat list of names to form the hierarchy needed to express an order with multiple items each of which may require multiple assets to personalize the result. There are no upper case letters in any field name. Field name qualifiers use \'_\' (underbar not a \'-\', dash) to separate name headers for use in different portions of the order. ','Fields','','inherit','closed','closed','','41-revision-5','','','2013-06-17 11:38:37','2013-06-17 18:38:37','',41,'http://storefronttest.rpiprint.com/partner/41-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(273,1,'2013-06-17 11:51:33','2013-06-17 18:51:33','To begin an order all of the following customer information must be supplied. Until this information is validated no information for the order is recorded. Once these values are complete an order-key is generated and is required in all POSTs and supplied in all responses until order-placed is received.\n<div align=\"center\">\n<table width=\"686\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"127\"></td>\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"228\"><b>Shipping label</b><b></b></td>\n<td width=\"331\"><b>Requirement </b><b>(optional)</b><b></b></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"127\"><b>order_pref</b></td>\n<td valign=\"top\" nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"228\">(opt) Partner reference information for this order. Holds a string that is accessible to the application when examining this order.</td>\n<td width=\"331\">Up to 1024 characters</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"127\"><b>order_note</b></td>\n<td valign=\"top\" nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"228\">(opt) Note that appears on shipping label.</td>\n<td width=\"331\">Up to 1024 characters</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"127\"><b>order_shipping</b></td>\n<td valign=\"top\" nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"228\">Shipping designator (UPS)</td>\n<td width=\"331\">Valid designator from list (USP,mail,FedEx?)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"127\"><b>label_name</b></td>\n<td valign=\"top\" nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"228\">Customer name</td>\n<td width=\"331\">[A-Za-z]+(\\\'[A-Za-z]+)?(\\s*\\-?\\s*[A-Za-z]+)?</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"127\"><b>label_email</b></td>\n<td valign=\"top\" nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"228\">Customer Email</td>\n<td width=\"331\">[A-Za-z0-9._%+-]+@[A-Za-z0-9.-]+\\.[A-Za-z]{2,4}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"127\"><b>label_phone</b></td>\n<td valign=\"top\" nowrap=\"nowrap\" width=\"228\">Customer Phone</td>\n